# Google OAuth Credentials
# Get these from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > Credentials
# 2. Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
# 3. **RECOMMENDED: Select "Desktop app" (NOT "Web application")**
# 4. Name it: "QuiteInbox Desktop Client"
# 5. Click "Create"
# 6. Copy the Client ID (and optionally Client Secret)
#
# Why "Desktop app" OAuth client?
# - Works perfectly with PKCE and localhost redirects
# - No need to configure authorized redirect URIs
# - Simpler setup for local development
# - Equally secure (PKCE provides the cryptographic protection)
#
# If using "Web application" OAuth client instead:
# - You MUST add to "Authorized redirect URIs": http://localhost:5173/oauth/callback
# - You MUST add to "Authorized JavaScript origins": http://localhost:5173
# - More configuration but works fine once set up correctly

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here.apps.googleusercontent.com
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here_optional